post_text: As part of Suicide Awareness Month, the California Department of Education and the San Diego Office of Education is hosting a Virtual Event. Students, please join live for the first ever LivingWorks virtual summit on September 15, 2020 from 1-2:00 PM. This event includes guest performers, speakers and stories from other students. The summit is available to all 7-12th grade students and following the event each student will be provided with the opportunity to register for an online Suicide Prevention Training to inspire and empower them to support a friend for family member that may be thinking about suicide.

Yuba-Sutter-Colusa United Way
August 11 at 2:33 PM ¬∑

Annual Grocery Outlet Independence From Hunger Drive totals! This is the third year Grocery Outlet in Yuba City has donated the receipts from it's annual "Freedom form Hunger" food drive to YSC United Way to provide funding for our local food pantries and the Yuba-Sutter Food Bank. This year more than $15,000 was raised at the store from shoppers and was distributed to 22 food pantries and the Yuba-Sutter Food Bank and YSC United Way provided to funds to the Yuba-Sutter COVID-19 Relief Task force for distribution! The three year total for receipts from the drive exceeds $32,000! In the picture from left to right are: YSC United Way Executive Director Bob Harlan; and Grocery Outlet co-owners Jeremy and Amy Delay.

shared_text:
California Department of Education
July 28 at 12:16 PM ¬∑

CDE has just released an online resource to help local educational agencies (LEAs) address questions related to distance learning pursuant to California Education Code 43500‚Äì43511 (resulting from Senate Bill 98). These Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) can be found on the CDE Distance Learning FAQs web page at https://www.cde.ca.gov/ci/cr/dl/distlearningfaqs.asp, and more FAQs will follow in the coming days.

Later this week, CDE will also release the Learning Continuity Plan Template, Instructions, and Guidance in addition to an FAQ for LEAs. The template is intended to support the planning that districts are already doing as they prepare to begin another academic year and hold to the promises of the Local Control Funding Formula. The Learning Continuity Plan replaces the LCAP for the 2020-21 school year.

As a reminder, CDE will host two upcoming webinars for LEAs to better understand Learning Continuity and Attendance Plans. Details can be found here: https://www.cde.ca.gov/fg/aa/lc/tuesdaysat2.asp.

Today is an amazing day !!!! ! 3 and 1/2 years ago my youngest son was diagnosed with leukemia! With so much love and support i want to thank you ! Because today william is cancer free !!! He had his last chemo appt today !!! Still a long road ahead . but both William Aubuchon and i are so proud of this amazing boy ! A true super hero in our eyes. We would like to thank everyone that has helped, thought , cared and loved my family and william thru this battle in our life .. And all we are asking is to share this amazing boy story so the world can see that even tho 2020 is so crazy, that on july 22 2020 william jr is CANCER FREE!!!

Also if you would like to celebrate him ringing the bell at u.c davis please let me know !

California Department of Education
June 8 at 9:07 AM ¬∑

Today, State Superintendent Tony Thurmond will release the CDE guidance document, ‚ÄúStronger Together: A Guidebook for the Safe Reopening of California‚Äôs Public Schools." During a news conference at 11:15 a.m. on Facebook Live, Thurmond and CDE leaders will walk through the document‚Äôs key tools and recommendations.

This guidance will serve as a road map of recommendations for schools as they work with their local public health officials and school communities to navigate next steps. Educational leaders will find recommendations for face coverings, physical distancing, and symptom screening should schools plan to provide some form of in-person instruction and distance learning. The document will also provide in-depth considerations for designing high-quality and equitable instructional practices for all students.
text:
California Department of Education
June 8 at 9:07 AM ¬∑

Today, State Superintendent Tony Thurmond will release the CDE guidance document, ‚ÄúStronger Together: A Guidebook for the Safe Reopening of California‚Äôs Public Schools." During a news conference at 11:15 a.m. on Facebook Live, Thurmond and CDE leaders will walk through the document‚Äôs key tools and recommendations.

This guidance will serve as a road map of recommendations for schools as they work with their local public health officials and school communities to navigate next steps. Educational leaders will find recommendations for face coverings, physical distancing, and symptom screening should schools plan to provide some form of in-person instruction and distance learning. The document will also provide in-depth considerations for designing high-quality and equitable instructional practices for all students.
